        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Oct 1. 73</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I thank you for the honour which you have done me by sending me your great work on Capital;<ref target="#foot.f1"/> &amp; I heartily wish that I was more worthy to receive it, by understanding more of the deep &amp; important subject of political economy. Though our studies have been so different, I believe that we both earnestly desire the extension of knowledge, &amp; that this in the long run is sure to add to the happiness of mankind.</p>
<p>I remain Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.5 that] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
            </div>
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The first volume of the second edition of Marx’s <hi rend="italic">Das Kapital</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5277.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Marx 1873</ref>) is in the Darwin Library–Down (later volumes were published only after Marx’s death).</note>
        </div>        
            
